Sri Lanka .
Galle, purch. Dr W. Ondaatje, 4 ovig. ♀♀ cl 9.5-10.6 mm (NHM 1882.19). — Mt. Lavinia, 16.XI.1928 , 5♂♂ cl 9.6-12.1 mm , 1 ovig. ♀ cl 10.1 mm (NHM). — Belligam, 1929, 10 ♂♂ , 18 ♀♀ (
NMW 19059
). — 1929, 2 ♂♂ (
NMW 19058
).

“The upper surface of the carapace and the anterior legs are of a more or less dark cinerous gray, the hands being marbled with a lighter rose-colour; the under surface of the carapace, like the ambulatory legs, except the white tarsi, are of a pale rose colour. The granules are all white.” (de 
Man 1881: 128
). “The body is dull brown to grey with greenish mottling on the lateral areas; ovig. females were mottled green all over […] The appendages were banded with green.” (
Tirmizi & Kazmi 1988: 108
).
